{
  "texts": [
    "In this Article, we harness light scattering through an off-the-shelf multimode fibre (MMF) to program generalized quantum circuits for transverse spatial photonic modes in dimensions up to seven.",
    "We apply these circuits for the manipulation of high-dimensional entangled states of light in multiple spatial-mode bases, demonstrating high-dimensional Pauli ℤ and Pauli 𝕏𝕏 gates, discrete Fourier transforms and random unitaries in the macro-pixel and orbital angular momentum spatial-mode bases 42, 54.",
    "Furthermore, in contrast to single-outcome technique harnesses random unitaries U j (such as a complex scattering system) interspersed with controllable phase planes P j implemented via SLMs, which provide programmability over the target circuit.",
    "c, A similar approach using multiplane light converters, where the random unitaries are replaced with free-space propagation F.",
    "https://doi.org/10.1038/s41567-023-02319-6 lens system."
  ]
}